{'text': 'The fact that most countries in the world have legalized drugs does not mean that we should legalize drugs in the US.'}
{'text': 'What if you were to choose a way to alleviate drug abuse in your community, but you had no idea how to legalize the drug in the first place?'}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs would have a beneficial effect on society in general, as the supply of drugs would be reduced.'}
{'text': "I realize that the war on drugs is a failure. I realize that the United States does not have a monopoly on the world's drugs."}
{'text': 'For some drugs, I think it is important to get rid of the prohibition; others, I believe it is better to make the drug legal.'}

{'text': 'When we legalize cigarettes, why not legalize liquor? Why not legalize chewing gum? Why not legalize chocolate bars and soft drinks? Why not legalize coffee and tea? Why not legalize heroin and cocaine?'}
{'text': 'By legalizing drugs, the government will have an easier time keeping track of all those drug users who are using drugs to escape the pain and suffering of their lives.'}
{'text': 'If cannabis is legalized and used as a medicine, then I think it would be a good idea to legalize alcohol and tobacco as well.'}
{'text': 'The point of legalization is not to make it easy for people to get drugs, but to reduce the amount of drugs that are available to people.'}
{'text': 'Why do we have to go through the lengthy process of reforming the tobacco and alcohol industries, and why do we have to do it in a so-called "free market environment?'}
{'text': 'If you really want to reduce the availability of drugs in our society, then you need to accept that there will be some people who will still want to sell drugs.'}
{'text': "The only way to really get rid of drug use is to stop the demand for drugs by making sure that drug usage isn't encouraged in our society."}
{'text': 'Legalization of drugs would have a very positive effect on public health. Right now, the government is paying people to commit suicide.'}
{'text': "Wouldn't it be better to do it the other way around?"}
{'text': 'If I found out that someone was doing drugs, what would I do if I found them?'}
{'text': "-Well, it's not too late, right?"}
{'text': "Who has the right to decide what drugs are legal and what ones aren't?"}

{'text': 'Why not legalize alcohol and tobacco too? Why not legalize cannabis? Why not legalize heroin? Why not legalize LSD? Why not legalize cocaine? Why not legalize methamphetamine? Why not legalize ecstasy?'}

{'text': 'Legalizing drugs will almost certainly get a lot of people hooked on drugs. This is a problem that cannot be solved by simply arresting people and telling them they need to stop using drugs.'}

{'text': "Imagine a scenario in which the government decides to allow people to grow and smoke marijuana and cocaine, without ever telling you that it's a bad idea. What would be the next logical step?"}
{'text': 'Why should there be only one option when it comes to drugs?'}
{'text': 'This will be the greatest thing that ever happened to the legalization of drugs. Drugs will be legal again, and this will lead to a complete end to drug abuse in our country.'}

{'text': "We should be looking at the potential negatives of legalizing drugs rather than considering the benefits. This way, we'd be more likely to find out what the actual negative effects of legalization might be."}
{'text': 'The government does not control the drug market. Even if the government did, it would be unable to limit the number of drug users because the drug market is so large.'}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you're also going to have to legalize sex and alcohol. That's just how the world works."}

{'text': 'I think that we should legalize marijuana, decriminalize everything else in the drug black market, and restrict the size of the drug market to people who are directly affected by it, such as first-time...'}
{'text': 'Given the current cost of prison, would you really want to jail someone for using drugs?'}
{'text': 'When people are able to access drugs legally, there will be less need for them to resort to drug dealers, and therefore, there will be less drug-related crime.'}
{'text': 'What if we legalize all drugs?" Would this make it easier for those who don\'t want to give up their drugs?'}
{'text': 'Would you rather have people buying drugs in pharmacies like vaccines, or would you prefer people buying the drugs themselves?'}
{'text': "It seems like a good idea to legalize drugs, but doesn't it seem like a better idea to legalize drugs for reasons that are more important than legalization?"}
{'text': "Maybe you don't want to legalize drugs because you think it will lead to the deaths of people who are still using drugs."}
{'text': 'The war on drugs has been a complete failure as far as actually reducing the amount of illegal drugs in the world.'}
{'text': 'As long as there is a black market for these substances, there will always be people willing to buy them from those who are willing to sell them to them.'}
{'text': "While we certainly need to decriminalize drugs and prostitution, I don't think that we need to legalize them, either. \xa0This isn't about freedom, it's about decentralization."}

{'text': "If we're going to legalize drugs, we should legalize them in a way that minimizes the harm they do, while also allowing people the freedom to choose whatever kind of drug they want to use."}
{'text': "I'd like to think that there are some people out there who might not agree with my stance on drug legalization."}
{'text': 'If a person breaks the law, he should face the consequences. If the consequences are prison, then by all means incarcerate.'}
{'text': "There's a lot of information out there that says that alcohol and cigarettes are more harmful than marijuana."}
{'text': "At the end of the day, the only thing that really matters is how much we want to spend. If we feel that we want to spend more, then let's do it."}
{'text': 'Legalization of drugs does not automatically lead to the end of drugs. If a government was to legalize drugs, then it would have a huge financial incentive to keep drugs illegal.'}
{'text': "We've already lost a war on drugs. Drugs are still illegal in many countries around the world."}
{'text': "Just because we have the right to do so, doesn't mean we have the right to do it the wrong way."}
